[2025-05-20 13:28:08,790] INFO: Result:  To create a cohesive dinosaur‐themed classroom, I first anchor the floor at the center and surround it with walls and a ceiling to define the room’s volume. The teaching zone sits at the north: the teacher’s desk and chair face south toward students, with the blackboard mounted on the north wall behind them. The student seating zone occupies the central floor in two rows of five desks, all oriented north, with clear 1 m aisles between rows and room edges. 

Decorative elements enliven the walls: dinosaur posters flank the east and west walls, murals adorn the south wall, and a dinosaur skeleton model stands in the northeast corner. Potted plants mark each corner on the floor. A bookshelf on the south wall anchors the rear, while a ceiling‐mounted projector above the board and six evenly distributed lights illuminate the space. Window curtains span the west wall, and waste bins sit near the teacher station and at the back center.
